### Issue

- **What did you do?**
Ran through the Movie Lens recommendation pipeline. 
Dataset can be found from AzureML gallery:
https://gallery.azure.ai/Experiment/Recommender-Movie-recommendation-3

- **What happened?**
The UserId was set to Int32 - so when running the training, I get an error:

> System.InvalidOperationException: 'Column 'UserId' with role MatrixColumnIndex should be a known cardinality U4 key, but is instead 'Int32''

- **What did you expect?**
Not to see U4 in the description as this tells me nothing. The error should say must be of KeyDataViewType. 

### Source code / logs
Here is the sample code to reproduce:
```
using Microsoft.ML;
using Microsoft.ML.Data;
using Microsoft.ML.Trainers;
using System;

namespace ConsoleApp36
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Hello World!");

            var mlContext = new MLContext();
            var loader = mlContext.Data.CreateTextLoader(new TextLoader.Options()
            {
                Columns = new TextLoader.Column[]
                {
                    new TextLoader.Column("UserId", DataKind.Int32, 0),
                    new TextLoader.Column("MovieId", DataKind.Int32, 1),
                    new TextLoader.Column("Rating", DataKind.Int32, 2),
                    new TextLoader.Column("Timestamp", DataKind.Int64, 3)
                },
                HasHeader = true,
                Separators = new char[] { ',' }
            });

            var data = loader.Load("{path to data}/Movie Ratings.csv");
            var pipeline = mlContext.Recommendation().Trainers.MatrixFactorization(new MatrixFactorizationTrainer.Options()
            {
                MatrixColumnIndexColumnName = "UserId",
                MatrixRowIndexColumnName = "MovieId",
                LabelColumnName = "Rating"
            });

            var model = pipeline.Fit(data);
            
        }
    }
}
```

Here is the line of code where this is occurring:
https://github.com/dotnet/machinelearning/blob/366332047340bdb12cf5fe2a11f9a6e257af9b84/src/Microsoft.ML.Recommender/RecommenderUtils.cs#L65

Consider this code snippet:
```
var defaultPipeline = ml.Transforms.Text.FeaturizeText("TextFeatures", "Text")
.Append(ml.Transforms.ProjectToPrincipalComponents("PC", "TextFeatures", null, 10))
.Append(ml.Transforms.DropSlots("ShortenedPC", "PC", new int[] { 0, 1}))  // drop slots 0 & 1
```
Currently its not possible bcs SlotDroppingTransform is not exposed. The workaround is to use CustomMapping which is bit cumbersome.
